Visual Upgrade Plan for Web Janggi
The goal is to transform the basic Janggi game into a visually premium, modern web experience using "Rich Aesthetics" and "Dynamic Design".

Proposed Changes
1. Aesthetic Overhaul (CSS & UI)
Background: Replace solid gray with a deep, elegant gradient (e.g., dark teal/slate) or a subtle texture to enhance contrast with the board.
UI Panels: Use Glassmorphism (translucent white/dark backgrounds with blur) for the "Turn" indicator and buttons.
Typography: Integrate a modern Korean font (e.g., 'Noto Serif KR' or Keep 'Apple SD Gothic Neo' but with better weight/spacing).
Layout: Center the board perfectly with a nice shadow/glow.
2. Board Rendering (Canvas)
Texture: Simulate a wood grain pattern or use a warm, high-quality solid color with a gradient vignette.
Grid: Sharper, maybe slightly glowing or etched lines.
Palace: distinct marking for the palace (X-box) with decorative corners if possible.
3. Piece Rendering (Canvas)
Shape: Octagonal design (traditional) or high-quality Circle with 3D bevel effect (gradients + shadow).
Typography: clear, bold characters.
Selection: Glow effect instead of just a colored outline.
Movement Guide: Subtle dots with pulsing animation for valid moves.
4. Animation System (JS)
Interpolation: Implement a basic animation loop (requestAnimationFrame) to slide pieces from (r1, c1) to (r2, c2) instead of teleporting.
Easing: Use an ease-out function for natural movement.
User Review Required
None at this stage, proceeding with standard "Make it attractive" best practices.
Verification Plan
Manual Verification
Check visual rendering of board and pieces.
Verify animations are smooth and piece lands correctly.
Ensure game logic remains intact (no regressions in moves).